New Jersey Devils (6-3-1, third in the Metropolitan Division) vs. Chicago Blackhawks (4-6, eighth in the Central Division)
Chicago; Sunday, 7 p.m. EST
FANDUEL SPORTSBOOK NHL LINE
: Devils -228, Blackhawks +183; over/under is 6.5
BOTTOM LINE: The Chicago Blackhawks and the New Jersey Devils hit the ice in an out-of-conference matchup.
Chicago had a 26-49-7 record overall and a 14-23-4 record in home games last season. The Blackhawks had a -97 goal differential last season, scoring 202 goals while allowing 299.
New Jersey had a 52-22-8 record overall and a 30-12-5 record in road games last season. The Devils had a 21.9% power play success rate last season, scoring 49 goals on 224 chances.
